{"cursor":"20610","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nDespite numerous efforts to reduce or eliminate them, many nations continue to\nresearch and/or stockpile chemical weapon agents. Most states have joined the\nChemical Weapons Convention, which requires the destruction of all chemical\nweapons by 2012. Twelve nations have declared chemical weapons production\nfacilities and six nations have declared stockpiles of chemical weapons. All of\nthe declared production facilities have been destroyed or converted to civilian\nuse after the treaty went into force. According to the United States government,\nat least 17 nations currently have active chemical weapons programs.\n\nTo the right is a summary of the nations that have either declared weapon\nstockpiles, or are suspected of secretly stockpiling or possessing CW\nresearch programs.\n","linknr":326,"url":"Chemical_weapon_proliferation","recorded":1362560230,"links":22,"instances":["nerve_agent"],"pdf":["http://www.defenselink.mil/pubs/ptr20010110.pdf","http://www.anthrax.osd.mil/documents/library/proliferation.pdf","http://www.state.gov/documents/organization/52113.pdf"],"categories":["Chemical warfare","Chemical weapons demilitarization"],"headings":["Chemical weapon details, per nation","See also","References","Resources"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/WMD_world_map.svg/220px-WMD_world_map.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/89/Symbol_book_class2.svg/16px-Symbol_book_class2.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/48/Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg/16px-Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/23px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6c/Wiki_letter_w.svg/23px-Wiki_letter_w.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf